{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 00:22:05.035178", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of current condition\\n- Host-to-host connectivity is broken between pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) and pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24).\\n- The EBGP control plane across the Clos fabric (leaves, spines, super-spine) appears healthy with sessions established and routes exchanged as expected.\\n- The problem is localized to the access link/host pc_0_1 side.\\n\\nObserved symptoms and test evidence\\n- End-to-end reachability:\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 100% loss with “Destination Host Unreachable” generated by 172.16.1.19 (leaf_router_0_1 eth1), indicating the fabric can reach the destination leaf but that leaf cannot reach the host at 10.0.1.2.\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: “Network is unreachable” from pc_0_1 (no usable route/interface).\\n- Access/gateway checks:\\n  - pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1 (leaf_router_0_1 SVI): success (TTL 62), proving the fabric path between the two leaves is working.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.1.2: “Destination Host Unreachable” and ARP entry for 10.0.1.2 is INCOMPLETE, showing failure to resolve the host MAC on the 10.0.1.0/24 segment.\\n- Host interfaces and routing:\\n  - pc_0_0: eth0 UP, IP 10.0.0.2/24, default gateway 10.0.0.1 present; can ping its gateway successfully.\\n  - pc_0_1: eth0 DOWN, IP 10.0.1.2/24 configured but interface state DOWN; no routes installed; ethtool shows Link detected: no on eth0.\\n- Leaf SVI and link status:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 eth8 is UP with 10.0.1.1/24; ethtool shows Link detected: yes; RX packets 0 (no traffic received from host), TX minimal.\\n- Control-plane health (BGP):\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 8 neighbors, all Established, receiving 31 prefixes per neighbor.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 8 neighbors, all Established.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: 12 neighbors each, Established, receiving expected prefixes from leaves and super-spine.\\n  - super_spine_router_0: 32 neighbors, Established. Overall routing table sizes and prefix reception counts are consistent with a healthy EBGP fabric.\\n\\nAnomaly detection\\n- Abnormal behavior: pc_0_1 is unreachable across the fabric and even from its directly connected leaf due to L2 adjacency failure on the access link.\\n- The fabric itself shows no signs of control-plane failure; routing is converged.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Fault domain: Access segment between leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.1/24 on eth8) and host pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 on eth0).\\n- Faulty device/interface: pc_0_1 eth0.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- Root cause: pc_0_1’s interface eth0 is down (administratively or link-layer down). Evidence:\\n  - ip addr shows eth0 state DOWN.\\n  - ethtool on pc_0_1 eth0 reports Link detected: no.\\n  - No IP routes on pc_0_1, consistent with the interface being down.\\n  - On the leaf side, eth8 is UP with link detected yes, but ARP for 10.0.1.2 remains INCOMPLETE and there are no RX packets from the host, confirming the host is not responding at L2.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Traffic to/from 10.0.1.2 (pc_0_1) is fully impacted.\\n- Traffic within and across other pods/leafs appears nominal given healthy BGP sessions and successful inter-leaf reachability tests (e.g., pc_0_0 to 10.0.1.1).\\n\\nNo remediation steps are proposed per instructions., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='13112562-24ad-4f14-b93a-6dde15c33760'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
